# Dmytro's Coding Rules & Preferences

## Java Standards
- Use try-with-resources for all resource management
- Prefer modern Java practices (streams, records, Optional)
- Always add proper null checks before accessing objects
- Use ObjectMapper for JSON instead of String.format()
- Set UTF-8 charset explicitly for JSON responses
- Don't close servlet response streams manually

## Testing Standards
- Use JUnit 5 + Mockito for unit tests
- Descriptive test method names: `methodName_WhenCondition_ShouldResult`
- Follow Given-When-Then structure in tests
- Include both success and failure scenarios
- Test edge cases and null inputs

## Code Style
- IntelliJ IDEA-style syntax highlighting preferences
- Method names: Blue (#4FC1FF)
- Variables/method calls: White (#FFFFFF)  
- Fields: Purple (#9876AA)
- Keywords: Orange (#CC7832)
- Strings: Green (#6A8759)
- Comments: Gray italic (#808080)

## Architecture Preferences
- Use Spring Boot best practices
- Proper exception handling with custom exceptions
- RESTful API design
- Secure JWT implementation
- Redis caching with appropriate annotations

## IDE Settings
- Auto-collapse imports by default
- Show variable values inline during debugging
- UTF-8 encoding everywhere
- Auto-expand debug variables 